			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Unfortunately, bitching is generally a wasted effort.  Having run various online games for the better part of twelve years [starting with MUDs and up through graphical MMORPG], I can tell you that without fail administrators and developers are always convinced they're right and will only admit their grand vision for the game isn't achievable when it is far too late for the game to recover.  Yes, I've been guilty of it myself.
<br />

<br />
Generally the bitching and whining is written off as "power players" pissed because they got gimped/nerfed/downgraded/equalized/assraped/etc rather than people having valid concerns or problems with the implemented change.
<br />

<br />
Was the crafting system in place on the test server?  If so, why the hell didn't we hear about it before the release?  That would have been a better time for everyone to bitch.  Occasionally [very very very rarely actually] people will listen to you when testing and effect a change.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, as I said in the SWG forum, SB is dying faster than a crack whore with cancer.  I'm going to ride this into the ground and then move on.<br />_________________<br /><strong>Shadowbane</strong>
